data.headline: Aamir Khan
data.description: Aamir Khan is a protective older brother to Kamala, but remains unaware of her extracurricular activities as the Super Hero, Ms. Marvel.

data.headline: Aero
data.description: With the power of the wind at her command, Lei Ling is the master of the sky and the protector of Shanghai!

data.headline: Aero
data.description: Mutant Melody Guthrie manifests the power of flight and studies at the Xavier Institute until the fateful M-Day that depowered her and many other mutants.

data.headline: Agatha Harkness
data.description: The centuries old witch Agatha Harkness uses her potent spells to protect others and train powerful beings in the art of magic.

data.headline: Agent Mobius
data.description: Mobius is an agent for the Time Variance Authority who specializes in the investigations of particularly dangerous time criminals.

data.headline: El Águila
data.description: A mutant, skilled fencer, and hand-to-hand combatant, El Águila is a swashbuckling force to be reckoned with.

data.headline: Aisha
data.description: Aisha, Muneeba Khan's grandmother, moved to Karachi, Pakistan, following the Partition of India with her family.

data.headline: Ajak
data.description: The Eternal Ajak is the spiritual leader of the group, guiding the Eternals on their mission from their home planet to Earth to defend humankind from the predatorial Deviants.

data.headline: Alex Wilder
data.description: The intelligent and observant Alex Wilder is able to bring the Runaways together, despite not having the superpowered abilities or tech that his friends possess.

data.headline: Alphonso Mackenzie
data.description: Alphonso "Mack" Mackenzie is a mechanic, engineer and field agent, with a complicated relationship with S.H.I.E.L.D. who has proven loyal to the cause and handy with a shotgun ax.

data.headline: Brawn
data.description: One of the smartest people on Earth, teenager Amadeus Cho has embraced his new Hulk-like powers as the hero called Brawn.

data.headline: Ammit
data.description: The sphinx Ammit serves the Egyptian goddess Ma’at, asking riddles of sinners and devouring them if they fail to answer correctly.

data.headline: Aneka
data.description: A high-ranking member of the Dora Milaje, Captain Aneka leads by example and serves the country she loves.

data.headline: Angar the Screamer
data.description: Master of the Mind Storm, Angar the Screamer uses his sonic scream to illicit hallucinations that disable his opponents, allowing him to commit crimes and escape custody.

data.headline: Angela
data.description: Angela is the firstborn daughter of Odin and Freyja, spirited away as an infant to the realm of Heven, where she becomes Leader of the Hunt.

data.headline: Dr. Annabelle Riggs
data.description: Dr. Annabelle Riggs: Archeologist. Adventurer. Bound to Valkyrie. Fearless Defender.

data.headline: Ant-Man
data.description: Ex-con Scott Lang finds a new lease on life, and a chance to redeem himself in the eyes of his daughter, after taking over the mantle of Ant-Man.

data.headline: Anubis
data.secondary_text: Anpu (Egyptian translation; Anubis is the Greek translation of his name)

data.headline: Att-Lass
data.description: Att-Lass is Starforce's stealth and infiltration specialist.

data.headline: Attuma
data.description: Attuma the Barbarian is the Lord of the Murky Depths, and frequent conqueror of Atlantis.

data.headline: Pug
data.description: Ex-bouncer turned lawyer Augustus “Pug” Pugliese practices law for Goodman, Lieber, Kurtzburg & Book, one of the most prestigious law firms on the East Coast.

data.headline: Auran
data.description: After undergoing Terrigenesis and becoming Inhuman, Auran becomes a savage martial artist and tactician, mercilessly defeating her foes.

data.headline: Axum
data.secondary_text: Daniel "Danny" Broughton; legally changed to Daniel Axum

data.headline: Ayo
data.description: A rebellious Dora Milaje initiate, Ayo becomes one of Wakanda’s fiercest fighters.

data.headline: Bakuto
data.description: A leader of the Hand, Bakuto passes on his teachings while also working to gain power.

data.headline: Zemo
data.description: Fueled by revenge, Zemo blames the Avengers for their role in his family’s deaths and uses every skill in his arsenal to take down the arrogant Super Heroes.

data.headline: Beautiful Dreamer
data.description: The mutant Dreamer is able to manipulate minds, implanting false memories that can either comfort or terrorize.

data.headline: Beta Ray Bill
data.secondary_text: Bill; legally changed to Beta Ray Bill

data.headline: Big Wheel
data.secondary_text: Axel Weele; legally changed to Jackson Weele

data.headline: Black Bolt
data.description: The Inhuman King Black Bolt reigns in silence, as he could level cities with a single word due to his sonic powers.

data.headline: Black Cat
data.description: Black Cat follows in the footsteps of her father learning the tricks of the trade for burglary, eventually losing her criminal ways to fight for the greater good.

data.headline: Cull Obsidian
data.description: A brutal and brutish follower of Thanos, this massively strong warrior will do what is needed to accomplish his master’s goals.

data.headline: Black Jack Tarr
data.description: Spy master Black Jack Tarr always strikes true when it comes to defending his country from career criminals.

data.headline: Black Knight
data.description: Burdened by a heavy past and wielding the Ebony Blade, Dane Whitman forges a new legacy as the Black Knight.

data.headline: Black Mariah
data.description: Ex-gang member and head of a drug-dealing enterprise, Black Mariah clashes with Luke Cage when her drugs get into the hands of one of his friends.

data.headline: Black Panther
data.description: T’Challa is the king of the secretive and highly advanced African nation of Wakanda - as well as the powerful warrior known as the Black Panther.

data.headline: Black Widow
data.description: Natasha Romanoff, separated from the now-fractured Avengers, confronts the dark path she took to becoming a spy and assassin, as well as events that followed.

data.headline: Yelena
data.description: A product of the Red Room’s ruthless training programs, this fiery assassin has a secret history with the Black Widow that she is determined to address.

data.headline: Blade
data.description: Himself a half-human/half-vampire, "Daywalker" Eric Brooks has honed his abilities to hunt down the undead who have long terrorized mankind.

data.headline: Blink
data.description: Mutant teleporter Blink helps her fellow mutants get in and get out before their foes know what has happened.

data.headline: Blue Marvel
data.description: Once a Golden Age guardian, the Blue Marvel returns to his Super Hero roots when called upon, using his anti-matter powers to defend people and the planet as an Avenger.

data.headline: Bron-Char
data.description: The Starforce team's muscle, Bron-Char uses brute force against the Skrulls.

data.headline: Bruno Carrelli
data.description: With a genius-level intellect, Bruno Carrelli uses his skills in science to create technology to help his best friend Kamala Khan, AKA Ms. Marvel, fight crime.

data.headline: Bulldozer
data.description: Super Villain Henry Camp is Bulldozer, the head-butting, mystically-empowered human who joins the Wrecking Crew to commit criminal acts.

data.headline: Cable
data.description: Sent to the future to survive a deadly infection, the cybernetically enhanced mutant Cable returns to the present and helps the X-Men.

data.headline: Calavera
data.secondary_text: Calavera (unrevealed if this is first or last name)

data.headline: Caliban
data.description: Abandoned and lonely, mutant Caliban often works with groups of heroes to utilize his ability to hunt down other mutants.

data.headline: Captain America
data.description: Recipient of the Super Soldier serum, World War II hero Steve Rogers fights for American ideals as one of the world’s mightiest heroes and the leader of the Avengers.

data.headline: Captain America
data.secondary_text: William Burnside (legally changed it to "Steven Rogers")

data.headline: Captain Marvel
data.description: Carol Danvers becomes one of the universe's most powerful heroes when Earth is caught in the middle of a galactic war between two alien races.

data.headline: Cecilia Reyes
data.description: When she was only six years old, Cecilia Reyes saw her father gunned down in a drive-by shooting. From that moment on, she dedicated her life to becoming a medical doctor.

data.headline: Chase Stein
data.description: Discovering his parents are up to no good, Chase Stein goes on the run with his friends, wielding special fistigons to fight when necessary.

data.headline: Claire Temple
data.description: Claire Temple, medical doctor and superhuman physiology expert, uses her knowledge and experience to treat Super Heroes and do no harm, though harm comes to her—hazards of the job.

data.headline: Cloak
data.description: Tyrone Johnson is able to access incredible powers that provide him with the ability to teleport and a connection with Tandy Bowen/Dagger.

data.headline: Collective Man
data.secondary_text: Han, Chang, Lin, Sun and Ho Tao-Yu

data.headline: The Collector
data.description: Offbeat alien Taneleer Tivan seeks both objects and living creatures that he finds of interest for his massive collection, including unwilling participants and dangerous weapons.

data.headline: Colleen Wing
data.description: Detective Colleen Wing utilizes her expertise in martial arts to fight crime alongside her friends and allies.

data.headline: Corvus Glaive
data.description: A loyal follower of Thanos, Corvus Glaive is a force to be reckoned with as he relentlessly strikes against those in his path.

data.headline: Cottonmouth
data.description: Pimp, business man, and drug lord, Cornell Cottonmouth is a force to be reckoned with, using his mouth full of razor sharp teeth to intimidate and threaten his foes.

data.headline: Crystal
data.description: The Inhumans Princess and sister of Queen Medusa, Crystal controls the elements with her Terrigen based powers. A friend of many heroes and mother to her daughter, Luna.

data.headline: Cuckoo
data.secondary_text: Kay Cera (possibly changed from an unrevealed name)

data.headline: Dagger
data.description: Tandy Bowen has found herself able to create beautiful yet dangerous daggers of light, while also forging an unbreakable bond with Tyrone Johnson/Cloak.

data.headline: Darcy Lewis
data.description: Earning college credit, intern Darcy Lewis assists Dr. Jane Foster in studying Einstein-Rosen Bridges, discovering that they are portals to another world full of gods and villains.

data.headline: Daredevil
data.description: Blinded in a childhood accident, attorney-at-law Matt Murdock protects Hell’s Kitchen as the masked vigilante, Daredevil.

data.headline: Dazzler
data.description: Alison Blaire constantly struggles to balance her life as a singer and a Super Hero. In her search for the perfect life she's joined the X-Men, Excalibur, and even S.H.I.E.L.D.!

data.headline: Deadpool
data.description: Ever-quipping mercenary Wade Wilson’s healing factor—and big mouth—make him one of the most relentlessly wisecracking heroes in the universe.

data.headline: Dennis "Buck" Bukowski
data.description: Cocky Assistant District Attorney strives to win cases against his rival in the courtroom, Gamma-powered lawyer Jennifer Walters, AKA She-Hulk.

data.headline: Derek Bishop
data.description: Derek Bishop, father to Kate Bishop, AKA Hawkeye, is a wealthy and influential person in the publishing industry, who is also involved in criminal activities.

data.headline: Devil Dinosaur
data.description: The mutated Devil Dinosaur hails from an alternate reality and is fiercely loyal to those he connects with - and a big problem for those who oppose him.

data.headline: Diamondback
data.description: Criminal Willis Stryker is a member of the Syndicate and uses his expert knife combat and throwing skills to defeat his biggest foe, Luke Cage.

data.headline: Doctor Doom
data.description: The egostical and maniacal Dr. Doom uses his brilliant scientific mind to augment his own power and quest for control.

data.headline: Doctor Erik Selvig
data.description: Dr. Erik Selvig, astrophysicist and professor, contributes his substantial knowledge to help the Avengers defeat their foes.

data.headline: Doc Ock
data.description: Brilliant scientist and perennial foe of Spider-Man, Dr. Otto Octavius AKA Doc Ock must learn to free his mind from his tentacles in order to regain control.

data.headline: Doctor Strange
data.description: Formerly a renowned surgeon, Doctor Stephen Strange now serves as the Sorcerer Supreme—Earth’s foremost protector against magical and mystical threats.

data.headline: Domino
data.description: Given good luck thanks to her powers, Neena Thurman has served as both a dangerous mercenary and a tough and resilient hero.

data.headline: Dormammu
data.description: Originating in the aptly-named Dark Dimension, this incredibly powerful being has ominous plans for Earth and those who live there.

data.headline: Dr. Arthur Harrow
data.description: Seeing humans as healthy specimens to experiment upon and cure his painful paralysis, Dr. Arthur Harrow stops at nothing to be free of his suffering.

data.headline: Drax
data.description: Drax uses his super strength and combat skills to destroy any enemies of the galaxy.

data.headline: Druig
data.description: Druig has the powerful ability to control the minds of humans with his cosmic energy, which at times makes it difficult to determine if he’s friend or foe.

data.headline: Ebony Maw
data.description: Ruthlessly carrying out his master's orders, Ebony Maw uses his formidable powers to enforce Thanos' rule.

data.headline: Eclipse
data.description: A member of the Mutant Underground, Marcos Diaz uses his light-based abilities to protect those he loves and help build a better future.

data.headline: Ego
data.description: Ancient and unbelievably powerful, Ego has the power of an entire planet at his disposal.

data.headline: Elaine Banner Walters
data.description: Elaine Banner Walters is the mother of Gamma-powered lawyer Jennifer Walters, AKA She-Hulk, and aunt to scientist and green behemoth Bruce Banner, AKA the Hulk.

data.headline: Electro
data.description: Max Dillon AKA Electro comes back stronger than ever.

data.headline: Elektra

image.alt: Elektra (Elektra Natchios) In Comics Character Card

data.description: Trained by the Hand to become an assassin, Elektra Natchios works as a deadly mercenary for anyone willing to pay her price.

data.headline: Elsa Bloodstone
data.description: Elsa Bloodstone takes up the family mantel of kicking serious monster butt, and becomes the world’s cutest, and deadliest, monster hunter.

data.headline: Emil Nikos
data.description: Biochemist Emil Nikos uses his intelligence to assist his best friend and colleague Dr. Michael Morbius until an experiment goes horribly wrong, resulting in deadly consequences.

data.headline: Enchantress
data.description: Amora is a powerful sorceress known as the Enchantress, famous for her beauty and infamous for her heartless scheming.

data.headline: Erik Killmonger
data.description: Raised in America, the man known as Erik Killmonger returns to his father's home of Wakanda determined to overthrow T'Challa and rule the nation himself.

data.headline: Eson
data.description: Eson the Searcher is one of the Celestials, an extraterrestrial giant that exists beyond the conventional understanding of space and time.

data.headline: Skurge
data.description: Asgardian warrior turned Executioner under Hela's command, Skurge deals with internal conflict as to whether he should save his people or exploit his newfound power.

data.headline: Filius
data.secondary_text: Filius (presumably Omen is his last name)

data.headline: Flag-Smasher
data.description: Flag-Smasher desires the destruction of America and all the nations of the world who have othered one another, and fulfills that desire using violent means.

data.headline: Foggy Nelson
data.description: Lawyer Foggy Nelson is often distracted from his legal duties because he worries about the safety of his best friend, Daredevil.

data.headline: Franklin Richards
data.description: Empowered with psionic and reality-manipulation abilities from his Super Hero parents Susan Storm and Reed Richards, Franklin Richards is one of the most powerful mutants.

data.headline: Frenchie
data.description: Former mercenary turned constant companion to Moon Knight, Jean-Paul DuChamp is a loyal friend and experienced pilot.

data.headline: Freyja
data.description: Before becoming the Asgardian Goddess of Marriage and All-Mother, Freyja was a Vanir Goddess.

data.headline: Friendly Neighborhood Spider-Man
data.description: Our friendly neighborhood hero swings into the MCU in his iconic suit.

data.headline: Frog-Man
data.description: Hero. Foodie. Avenger. Eugene Patilio is Frog-Man, who leaps into danger, believing destiny calls on him to save the world.

data.headline: Gaea
data.secondary_text: Unrevealed; Gaea is her Greek name

data.headline: Gamora
data.description: Raised by Thanos to be a living weapon, Gamora seeks redemption as a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy, putting her extraordinary fighting abilities to good use.

data.headline: Batroc
data.description: The bombastic baddie and legendary kickboxer Batroc leaps into action, mostly as a paid mercenary, but also enjoys a good fight.

data.headline: Gertrude Yorkes
data.description: The sarcastic and political Gert uses her telepathic link to Old Lace, her pet dinosaur to assist the Runaways.

data.headline: Ghost Rider
data.description: Making a demonic deal to save a loved one, biker Johnny Blaze now finds himself cursed to transform into the embodiment of the Spirit of Vengeance.

data.headline: Ghost Rider
data.description: A Ghost Rider-turned-Spirit Rider, the Apache-born Kushala is the Sorcerer Supreme of the 1800s who gets stranded in modern times.

data.headline: Ghost Rider
data.description: Young LA mechanic Robbie Reyes finds himself transformed into hell on four wheels as he becomes a new incarnation of Ghost Rider.

data.headline: Ghost-Spider
data.description: In an alternate universe, Gwen Stacy is bitten by a radioactive spider and becomes a super heroine.

data.headline: Gilgamesh
data.description: The powerful Eternal Gilgamesh is a fierce warrior remembered throughout history for his legendary battles.

data.headline: Goose the Cat
data.description: The friendliest and furriest resident of Project Pegasus, Goose is the affectionate tabby cat that joins Carol Danvers and Nick Fury on their adventure.

data.headline: Gorgon
data.description: The enforcer of the Inhuman Royal Family thanks to the Terrigen Mists, Gorgon's mighty strength and powerful hooved legs unleash shockwaves on his foes.

data.headline: Grandmaster
data.description: Everything is a game to this cosmic entity, who loves to pit beings against each other for his own amusement.

data.headline: Green Goblin
data.description: During a brutal battle with his greatest foe Spider-Man, Norman Osborn’s clothes are torn away revealing the original Goblin armor with a few lethal upgrades; glider and all.

data.headline: Groot
data.description: This sentient alien tree branches out of his comfort zone to help the Guardians of the Galaxy keep the people of the universe safe.

data.headline: Gwenpool
data.description: Medium-aware Gwendolyn Poole enters the universe of fiction to escape her unsatisfying life and holds knowledge of the entire Marvel Universe.

data.headline: H.E.R.B.I.E.
data.secondary_text: Humanoid Experimental Robot B-Type Integrated Electronics

data.headline: Harold Meachum
data.description: Founder of Rand Enterprises, Harold Meachum makes numerous sacrifices, including the death of his colleague Wendell Rand, to reach the highest levels of success.

data.headline: Hawkeye
data.description: A master marksman and longtime friend of Black Widow, Clint Barton serves as the Avengers’ amazing archer.

data.headline: He Who Remains
data.description: The last living creature in all eternity, He Who Remains sows destiny’s seeds by creating beings of pure knowledge, the Time-Keepers, who would safeguard the next cycle of time.

data.headline: Heimdall
data.description: An all-seeing Asgardian in charge of guarding the Rainbow Bridge known as the Bifrost, Heimdall's keen skills serve him well as a first line of defense.

data.headline: Hela
data.description: With family ties to the rulers of Asgard, Hela seeks power (and followers) for herself.

data.headline: Hellcat
data.description: The all-American Patsy Walker adopts the name Hellcat and is happy to be a Super Hero, as she has always revered them.

data.headline: Hepzibah
data.secondary_text: A combination of odors unintelligible to humans

data.headline: Hercules
data.description: The legendary Greek demigod and Prince of Power Hercules is a long-time Avenger and nigh-invincible, fighting on the side of good.

data.headline: High Evolutionary
data.description: Playing god, the High Evolutionary demands humanity’s evolution and, through genetic experimentation, creates anthropomorphic beings but does not covet his creations.

data.headline: Hildegarde
data.description: Asgardian warrior and one of Odin’s hand-picked Valkyrie, Hildegard, carries out great tasks for her homeland and yearns to slay any who oppose it.

data.headline: Hope Summers
data.description: Known as the Mutant Messiah, Hope is destined to save the entire mutant race or destroy the world.

data.headline: The Wasp
data.description: Showing the same scientific and heroic aptitude as her parents, the hero springs into action as the unstoppable Wasp.

data.headline: Horde
data.secondary_text: Horacio Carrenas, Elmira Phillips, Joe Famiglia, Floyd Henderson, a dog named Bacon, other unidentified individuals

data.headline: Howard Stark
data.description: Brilliant engineer, inventor, businessman, and founder of Stark Industries, Howard Stark is the mastermind behind the company that his son, Tony Stark, will one day inherit.

data.headline: Hulk
data.description: Dr. Bruce Banner lives a life caught between the soft-spoken scientist he’s always been and the uncontrollable green monster powered by his rage.

data.headline: Human Torch
data.description: Fiery and hotheaded, the Human Torch burns up the sky with an unquenchable love of adventure and always has the backs of his family, the Fantastic Four.

data.headline: Hunger
data.description: The Vampiric being Hunger satiates his bloodlust by taking lives and siring his children of the night, though his true ends remain a mystery.

data.headline: Hunter B-15
data.description: Hunter B-15 is a high-ranking Hunter, determined to find and delete The Variant for taking down TVA troops.

data.headline: Ikaris
data.description: The powerful Eternal Ikaris is the moral, charismatic tactician of the group, tasked with keeping his team and humanity safe.

data.headline: Impossible Man
data.secondary_text: Poppupians have no names; they know who they are

data.headline: Inferno
data.description: Dante is a brooding, dark loner who alienates his teammates but makes girls swoon.

data.headline: Invisible Woman
data.description: The formidable heroine Invisible Woman uses her powers of invisibility to protect Earth and acts as the leading maternal figure of the Fantastic Four.

data.headline: Iron Fist
data.description: Trained in ways of martial arts at K'un-Lun, Danny Rand becomes the Immortal Iron Fist and uses his incredible abilities to defend others.

data.headline: Melina
data.description: Melina is a highly trained spy who has been cycled through the Red Room’s Widow program four times.

data.headline: Iron Man
data.description: Genius. Billionaire. Philanthropist. Tony Stark's confidence is only matched by his high-flying abilities as the hero called Iron Man.

data.headline: Ironheart
data.description: Teenage super genius Riri Williams has taken Tony Stark's armor and reverse engineered it, adding her own modifcations, and becoming a hero in her own right!

data.headline: J. Jonah Jameson
data.description: When William Goodman's heirs put the Daily Bugle up for sale, J. Jonah Jameson tapped his last dollar and made the newspaper his own.

data.headline: Jemma Simmons
data.description: S.H.I.E.L.D. Academy's youngest and brightest, Dr. Simmons' brilliance and persistence has helped her survive the impossible.

data.headline: Jeryn Hogarth
data.description: Ruthless lawyer, Hogarth does whatever it takes to win cases and knows no loyalty other than loyalty to themselves.

data.headline: Jessica Jones
data.description: Working as a private investigator, Jessica Jones comes to the aid of those who need it, despite suffering severe trauma at the hands of the sadistic Kilgrave.

data.headline: Falcon
data.description: Human/falcon teenager Joaquin Torres becomes a hero, taking the moniker Falcon and becoming sidekick to the original holder of the alias, Sam Wilson.

data.headline: Bushmaster
data.description: A criminal mastermind who will go to great lengths to accomplish his goals.

data.headline: Jonathan Tremont
data.secondary_text: Unrevealed, legally changed to Jonathan Tremont

data.headline: Josiah X
data.secondary_text: Josiah al hajj Saddiq (legally changed, former legal name unrevealed)

data.headline: Joy Meachum
data.description: Joy is a savvy business leader from a family known for their ruthless approach, but when she inherits her father’s title, she gains his enemy the Iron Fist as well.

data.headline: Kamran
data.description: After the Terrigen Mist transforms him, Kamran discovers his gifts of bioluminescence and biokinetic powers.

data.headline: Kang the Conqueror
data.description: Iron Lad. Rama-Tut. Scarlet Centurion. Immortus. The Master of Time. He has had many names across the timestream, but only one dominates them all: Kang the Conqueror.

data.headline: Karen Page
data.description: Karen Page is strong-willed, passionate, and kind—it's no wonder her associates Matt Murdock and Foggy Nelson fall for her.

data.headline: Karnak
data.description: A master of the martial arts and trusted member of the Inhuman Royal Family, Karnak is able to see the flaws and weaknesses in the world and exploit them to achieve his agenda.

data.headline: Karolina Dean
data.description: A powerful addition to the Runaways, Karolina Dean can manipulate light energy and take flight.

data.headline: Khonshu
data.description: Khonshu is the Heliopolis god of the moon and vengeance, working through his servant Marc Spector, the vigilante known as Moon Knight!

data.headline: Kingo
data.description: The boisterous Eternal Kingo, enamored with the idea of fame, has taken the most advantage of his centuries-long time on Earth.

data.headline: Kingpin
data.description: One of the most powerful criminals in New York City, Wilson Fisk rules the underworld with a signature blend of cruelty and charm.

data.headline: Ulysses Klaue
data.description: An ongoing enemy of Wakanda and its people, this clever criminal would replace his lost arm with a powerful weapon.

data.headline: Knull
data.description: The god of the abyss from the beginning of time, Knull has warred against the light, creating the Symbiotes to further his cause.

data.headline: Korath
data.description: Stoic, humorless and disciplined, Korath is second-in-command in the elite Starforce.

data.headline: Kraven the Hunter
data.description: Kraven the Hunter is a world-famous explorer and brutal game hunter who can never resist a challenge, especially one that involves taking down Spider-Man.

data.headline: Leap-Frog
data.description: Equipped with spring-loaded shoes, the larcenous Leap-Frog commits crimes, though his son may just inspire him to be a high-jumping hero.

data.headline: Leaper Logan
data.secondary_text: Logan (Unrevealed if this is his first or last name)

data.headline: Legion
data.description: David Haller attempts to balance his incredible mutant powers with the mental illness he lives with.

data.headline: Leiko Wu
data.description: An agent for the British secret service MI-6, Leiko Wu is an expert in Martial arts and firearms, though she betrays her country for a more criminal path.

data.headline: Leo Fitz
data.description: Leopold Fitz’s exceptional intelligence makes engineering look so easy, a monkey could do it.

data.headline: Living Lightning
data.description: Able to transform himself into electrical plasma, Living Lightning uses his electrokinesis powers to protect the planet alongside an assemblage of Earth’s mightiest heroes.

data.headline: Lizard
data.description: Doctor Connors AKA Lizard is back in his reptilian form, ready to take on Spider-Man.

data.headline: Lockjaw
data.description: As the loyal protector of the Inhuman Royal family, the giant dog Lockjaw can teleport himself and others near him anywhere in the universe.

data.headline: Loki
data.description: God of Mischief and brother to Thor, Loki’s tricks and schemes wreak havoc across the realms.

data.headline: Luke Cage
data.description: After developing bulletproof skin from a failed prison experiment, Luke Cage uses his power to protect the people of New York.

data.headline: Luke Jacobson
data.description: Luke Jacobson is a famous fashion designer who comes under the protection of Dakota North.

data.headline: Luna Snow
data.description: Luna Snow is a Korean pop singer and Super Hero who uses her ice-manipulation powers to protect people in the Pacific Rim and across the World.

data.headline: M
data.secondary_text: Monet Yvette Clarisse Maria Therese St. Croix

data.headline: M.O.D.O.K.
data.description: Created by A.I.M., the Mental Organism Designed Only for Killing uses his mind powers and incredible intellect to live up to his name.

data.headline: Magik
data.description: Magik is a powerful sorceress and mutant able to teleport across time and space who suffers from internal demons but remains an angel at her core.

data.headline: Magneto
data.description: Using his mighty ability to control magnetic fields, the one called Magneto fights to help mutants replace humans as the world's dominant species.

data.headline: Magus
data.description: Emerging from a cocoon, the being known as Adam Warlock defies his creators' intentions and proves to be an important cosmic entity.

data.headline: Makkari
data.description: With her cosmic-powered super-speed, Makkari scouts planets for the Eternals, a group of ancient, immortal beings working on behalf of the Celestials.

data.headline: Malcolm Powder
data.description: Trusted friend and advisor to the private investigator Jessica Jones. Malcolm is a shoulder to lean on, whetever Jessica realizes it or not.

data.headline: Malekith
data.description: The Dark Elf of Svartalfheim, Malekith uses his magic and trickery to bring war to all of the Ten Realms.

data.headline: Mallory Book
data.description: Mallory Book: The barracuda lawyer with supermodel looks.

data.headline: Man-Bull
data.description: The Man-Bull is a bullheaded humanoid who commits crimes and ruthlessly rampages until the cows come home.

data.headline: Mantis
data.description: Mantis uses her powers to protect the galaxy against those who would seek to harm it.

data.headline: Maria Hill
data.description: Ruthless, determined, and efficient, Maria Hill makes an excellent second-in-command to Nick Fury.

data.headline: Maria Rambeau
data.description: A former test fighter pilot and Carol Danvers' best friend, Maria is a strong-minded and loyal confidante.

data.headline: Martine Bancroft
data.description: As fiancée to her beloved Dr. Michael Morbius, Martine Bancroft is intelligent and utterly dedicated to him, so much so that she becomes a vampire to never leave his side.

link.title: Master of the Four Winds (Timothy Lee)

data.headline: Maximus
data.description: This incredibly intelligent Inhuman continually attemps to overthrow his older brother Black Bolt to become King of the Inhumans.

data.headline: Medusa
data.description: Queen of the Inhumans and wife of Black Bolt, Medusa posesses and controls prehensile hair that is tougher than steel.

data.headline: Melinda May
data.description: As one of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s deadliest fighters, Agent May lives up to her nickname—"The Cavalry."

data.headline: Mercurio
data.secondary_text: Mercurio (name in his own language is unknown)

data.headline: Micro
data.description: Tech genius and hacker also known as Microchip, David Lieberman is the mastermind behind the Punisher's weaponry and gadgets.

data.headline: Midnight Man
data.description: The Midnight Man is a world-renowned art thief, who eludes authorities and holds his own against vigilantes like Moon Knight.

data.headline: Minn-Erva
data.description: Starforce's talented sniper, Minn-Erva is deadly from near and far.

data.headline: Miss Minutes
data.description: Hey y’all! Miss Minutes keeps the Time Variance Authority ticking like clockwork, in more ways than one.

data.headline: Mister Fantastic
data.description: Genius Reed Richards leads the Fantastic Four with the ability to stretch around a problem and expand upon the perfect solution.

data.headline: Misty Knight
data.description: Martial artist, detective, and one of the leaders of Heroes for Hire, Misty Knight's bionic arm possesses superhuman strength allowing her to battle even the toughest of foes.

data.headline: Mockingbird
data.description: Scientist. Super Hero. Spy. Dr. Barbara “Bobbi” Morse has done it all, and then some, as the costumed Avenger known as Mockingbird.

data.headline: Modred the Mystic
data.description: Modred the Mystic, sometimes emissary to the Elder God Chthon, is a powerful sorcerer corrupted by the ancient spellbook, the Darkhold.

data.headline: Moira Brandon
data.description: Moria Brandon makes a name for herself in the 1920s playing heroic leads like Cleopatra and Joan of Arc, but it isn’t until her later years that she gets the role of a lifetime.

data.headline: Molly Hayes
data.description: The youngest member of the Runaways is also the strongest; Molly possesses super human strength, an ability of which she is very proud.

data.headline: Monica Rappaccini
data.description: Monica Rappaccini is a ruthless biochemist who stops at nothing short of experimenting on her own daughter to attain scientific advancements.

data.headline: Moon Girl
data.description: Young genius and Inhuman Lunella Lafayette displays bravery beyond her years, using her vast intelligence and her telepathic link with Devil Dinosaur to become a hero.

data.headline: Moon Knight
data.description: A mild-mannered gift-shop employee, becomes plagued with blackouts and memories of another life.

data.headline: Morbius, The Living Vampire
data.description: Accidentally turning himself into a vampire, Michael Morbius finds himself torn between his human and monstrous natures.

data.headline: Morris Walters
data.description: Sheriff Morris Walters is a dedicated lawman who seeks justice for those wronged and has it out for She-Hulk when she first emerges as a seemingly savage killer.

data.headline: Mr. Frost
data.secondary_text: Unrevealed (Frost could potentially be his last name)

data.headline: Mr. Negative
data.description: The Chinese-born Mister Negative uses his control of both the lightforce and darkforce to expand his criminal empire, even while his kinder dual persona helps the community.

data.headline: Ms. Marvel
data.description: Kamala is a fan of most Super Heroes...especially her mentor, Captain Marvel. She has near encyclopedic knowledge of the Avengers and is not afraid to show it.

data.headline: Muneeba Khan
data.description: Muneeba Khan is a devoted wife and loving mother to her children, including her daughter Kamala Khan, AKA Ms. Marvel.

data.headline: Nakia
data.description: A formidable Wakandan, Nakia finds herself conflicted thanks to her feelings for T'Challa.

data.headline: Nakia Bahadir
data.description: Turkish-American and best friend to Kamala Khan, Nakia Bahadir is a fierce friend and social activist who cares about her community in Jersey City.

data.headline: Namor the Sub-Mariner
data.description: Half-human and half-Atlantean, the mutant Namor the Sub-Mariner has fought both with and against mankind.

data.headline: Namora
data.description: The Atlantean-Human Princess Namora is an adventurer who fiercely protects her underwater and surface brethren with her mutant aquatic powers.

data.headline: Namorita
data.secondary_text: Namorita (legally Namorita "Nita" Prentiss in surface society)

data.headline: Nebula
data.description: As a pirate and mercenary with her intentions set on conquering other empires, this daughter of Thanos is feared by many across the star systems.

data.headline: Nick Fury
data.description: A veteran S.H.I.E.L.D. operative, Nick Fury continues the legacy as one of the greatest super spies in the world.

data.headline: Nick Fury Jr.
data.description: A veteran S.H.I.E.L.D. operative, Nick Fury Jr. continues the legacy as one of the greatest super spies in the world

data.headline: Nico Minoru
data.description: After discovering the dark truth about her parents, Nico Minoru uses the powerful Staff of One to fight alongside her friends.

data.headline: Night Nurse
data.description: As the Night Nurse, Linda Carter heals and patches up Super Heroes in need.

data.headline: Nightshade
data.description: Tilda Johnson is gifted with a knack for science, using her intellect as an advantage in order to successfully commit crimes.

data.headline: Nova
data.description: Teenager Sam Alexander is the cosmic hero Nova and through his Nova helmet, he goes on to co-found the Champions to protect the universe and his home planet Earth.

data.headline: Nuke
data.description: Frank Simpson is an expert combatant and marksman and a past victim of Kilgrave's merciless control.

data.headline: Odin
data.description: The King of Asgard, Odin's immense wisdom helps him battle threats from both outside and within his realm.

data.headline: Okoye
data.description: One of Wakanda's greatest warriors, Okoye proudly protects her country's king alongside the Dora Milaje.

data.headline: Origin
data.secondary_text: Unrevealed (said to be unpronounceable by humans)

data.headline: Patriot
data.description: He values integrity, honesty, and order above all.

data.headline: Peggy Carter
data.description: An agent who fought alongside Captain America during World War II, Peggy Carter is a naturally born leader and staunch supporter of justice.

data.headline: Peni Parker
data.description: Co-pilot to the highly advanced SP//dr suit, Peni Parker is a young but unstoppable hero. She shares a genetic bond with a spider that helps operates her bionic armor.

data.headline: Pepper Potts
data.description: Virginia "Pepper" Potts handles the day-to-day business of running Stark Industries while Tony Stark focuses on developing new tech and his role within the Avengers as Iron Man.

data.headline: Phastos
data.description: The genius Phastos has nudged humanity’s technological advancements forward throughout the centuries while shielding his own brilliance.

data.headline: Phil Coulson
data.description: His devotion to upholding the legacy and duties of Super Heroes makes Phil Coulson the true definition of an agent of S.H.I.E.L.D.

data.headline: Piledriver
data.description: Piledriver utilizes super-strength and his over-sized hands to fight alongside his Super Villain squad, the Wrecking Crew.

data.headline: Pip the Troll
data.description: Cosmic teleporter Pip the Troll travels across the universe, often as a companion to Adam Warlock, and just as often engages in any debauchery he can find.

data.headline: Pizza Poppa
data.description: Pizza Poppa always gets paid.

data.headline: Polaris
data.description: Possessing magnetic powers, much like her father, Lorna Dane fights to help her fellow mutants fight against persecution.

data.headline: Porcupine
data.description: Using armor with high-velocity quills, U.S. Government weapons designer turned professional criminal, the Porcupine, becomes one of his generation’s first costumed Super Criminals.

data.headline: Proxima Midnight
data.description: Proxima Midnight conquers across the galaxy for her master Thanos, with her deadly spear ever ready to strike.

data.headline: The Punisher
data.description: When Frank Castle's beloved family is murdered, the ex-Marine becomes a vigilante with a uniquely brutal brand of justice.

data.headline: Kilgrave
data.description: With the ability to control people's minds, the sadistic Kilgrave earns his place as a truly reprehensible foe.

data.headline: Quake
data.description: With the ability to tap into the vibrations of any substance, skilled fighter Daisy Johnson, codename Quake, is a formidable foe to enemies of S.H.I.E.L.D.

data.headline: Bushman
data.description: Raoul Bushman: General, mercenary, terrorist, arms dealer, president of Burunda. If it’s criminal, Bushman has his hands in it.

data.headline: Ravonna Renslayer
data.description: Ravonna Renslayer is a respected judge in the Time Variance Authority, and one of few in rank to stand in the presence of the Time Keepers themselves.

data.headline: Red Dagger
data.description: A hometown hero in Karachi, Pakistan, Kareem is Laal Khanjeer, or the Red Dagger, protecting the innocent from dangerous threats.

data.headline: Red Guardian

image.alt: Red Guardian Alexei Shostakov David Harbour

data.description: Alexei is known most famously as Red Room’s answer to Captain America. He’s a Super-Soldier spy who has lived a lifetime of triumph during the Cold War.

data.headline: Red She-Hulk
data.description: Betty Ross is the greatest love of Bruce Banner's life, but also the daughter of his greatest enemy, General "Thunderbolt" Ross.

data.headline: Red Skull
data.description: Rising to power during World War II, Johann Schmidt become one of Earth’s most dangerous threats and one of Captain America’s greatest enemies.

data.headline: Ren Kimura
data.description: Dancer turned Inumhan, Ren Kimura is at first hunted for her abilities but soon finds powerful allies in the Fearless Defenders.

image.alt: Mason Rick Mason O. T. Fagbenle

data.headline: Rocket
data.description: As the weapons and tactical expert of the Guardians of the Galaxy, Rocket risks his hide to defend the cosmos.

data.headline: Rogue
data.description: Armed with the ability to temporarily absorb others’ powers and memories, this Mississippi runaway started her career as a villain before joining the X-Men to fight for good.

data.headline: Ronan
data.description: As a cruel and fanatical member of the Kree race, Ronan double-crossed Thanos in an attempt to keep the Power Stone for himself.

data.headline: Captain America
data.description: Sam Wilson, formerly the Falcon, takes on the mantle of Captain America as he teams up with his fellow Avengers.

data.headline: Sandman
data.description: Flint Marko AKA Sandman, stuck in fully sand form, must go with the flow to get himself back home.

data.headline: Saracen
data.description: The ruthless mercenary known as Saracen works for the Bessucho crime family and often goes toe to toe with one of the most brutal vigilantes of them all, the Punisher.

data.headline: Satana
data.description: Unlike her older brother, Satana embraced the teachings of her father, an arch demon commonly known as Satan.

data.headline: Scarlet Scarab
data.description: Scarlet Scarab is the protector of Egypt, defending his home from all foreign invasions.

data.headline: Wanda Maximoff
data.description: Notably powerful, Wanda Maximoff has fought both against and with the Avengers, attempting to hone her abilities and do what she believes is right to help the world.

data.headline: Scorpion
data.secondary_text: Thasanee Rappuccini; legally changed to Carmilla Black

data.headline: Sera
data.description: An Angel from Heven, Sera rebels against their strict rules and escapes to become her true self, a righteous mercenary skilled in spellcraft.

data.headline: Sersi
data.description: The humankind-loving Eternal Sersi delights in her mission stationed on Earth; she’s as happy working as a museum curator as she is saving humanity.

data.headline: Shades
data.description: Known for always wearing sunglasses, the criminal called Shades has proven to be a valuable asset for those he has worked for.

data.headline: Shadow King
data.description: A longtime threat able to possess those he wishes to, and do whatever he'd like with them, the Shadow King is a nearly unstoppable presence.

data.headline: Sharon Carter
data.description: Government spy Sharon Carter defends her country by joining intelligence agencies and follows orders… most of the time.

data.headline: Shocker
data.description: Herman Schultz combines his engineering intellect and past experience in criminality to embody the persona of "Shocker."

data.headline: Shuri
data.description: The younger sister of T'Challa, the Black Panther, Shuri astounds with her brilliant inventions, often providing key components to her brother's battles.

data.headline: Sif
data.description: A fierce warrior and loyal ally, the Lady Sif is always at the front of a battlefield when Asgard finds itself in trouble.

data.headline: Simon Stroud
data.description: CIA agent turned special investigator Simon Stroud often seeks out monsters, from Man-Wolf to Morbius, and he never gives up his hunt.

data.headline: Skaar
data.description: Born in fire. Raised by monsters. Destined to destroy. Enter Skaar, Son of Hulk!

data.headline: Skinner
data.secondary_text: Unrevealed (possibly Skinner or John, last name unrevealed)

data.headline: Smiling Tiger
data.description: The mystical mutate known as Smiling Tiger smiles when he kills, making him one deadly maniac.

data.headline: Speed
data.description: Thomas "Tommy" Shepherd can run at the speed of sound and manufacture vibrations to cause explosions. He often gets impatient waiting for the rest of the world to catch up to him.

data.headline: Spider-Man
data.description: Emerging from a universe in need of a new Spider-Man, a Brooklyn teen named Miles Morales rose to the challenge. Reluctant at first, he quickly earned the mantle of a Super Hero.

data.headline: Spider-Man
data.description: Bitten by a radioactive spider, Peter Parker’s arachnid abilities give him amazing powers he uses to help others, while his personal life continues to offer plenty of obstacles.

data.headline: Spider-Woman
data.description: Given her powers via genetic tampering as a child, Jessica Drew has gone on to work as a spy, private detective, and Super Hero.

data.headline: Sprite
data.description: The Eternal Sprite is the grandiose storyteller of the group who just so happens to possess the appearance of a 13-year-old girl.

data.headline: Squirrel Girl
data.description: Doreen's fun-loving, goofy persona comes naturally to her, but is also a great way to keep fear and anxiety at bay when the fate of the world hangs in the balance.

data.headline: Star-Lord
data.description: Leader of the Guardians of the Galaxy, Peter Quill, known as Star-Lord, brings a sassy sense of humor while protecting the universe from any and all threats.

data.headline: Starfox
data.description: Eros grew up on Titan alongside his brother Thanos, embracing all the pleasures that life has to offer. He laters becomes Starfox and an official member of the Avengers.

data.headline: Steel Serpent
data.description: Trained to fight in K'un-Lun, Davos is crushed by his failure to become the Iron Fist, and finds himself motivated by revenge.

data.headline: Stepford Cuckoos
data.secondary_text: Celeste, Esme (deceased), Irma (aka "Mindee"), Phoebe, Sophie (deceased) (surname unrevealed)

data.headline: Stick
data.description: Leader of The Chaste, a warrior order, Stick trains a generation of heroes and  fights alongside them to seek destruction of The Hand.

data.headline: Storm
data.description: Mutant Ororo Munroe confounds enemies of the X-Men by using her psionic abilities to manipulate the weather.

data.headline: Supergiant
data.description: Omnipotent and telepathic, Supergiant uses her abilities to take control over others and devour their intellect as a member of Thanos' Black Order.

data.headline: Sylvie Laufeydottir
data.description: Sylvie is the extremely capable and dangerous variant who just happens to be another version of Loki.

data.headline: Talos
data.description: Talos, perhaps the most cunning spy in all of the Skrull Empire, is a master of shapeshifting and intergalactic espionage.

data.headline: Taskmaster
data.description: Taskmaster is a masked assassin who carries out deadly missions on behalf of the Red Room.

data.headline: Taweret
data.description: Taweret is the goddess of childbirth and part of the Ennead, AKA the Egyptian gods.

data.headline: Thanos
data.description: The Mad Titan Thanos quests across the universe in search of the Infinity Stones, intending to use their limitless power for shocking purposes.

data.headline: The Amazing Spider-Man
data.description: The one and only Amazing Spider-Man webs his way into the MCU.

data.headline: The Locust
data.description: Proud inheritor of a heroic legacy stretching back centuries, the Locust is the protector of the lost and vulnerable.

data.headline: The Thing
data.description: Gruff and gung-ho Ben Grimm rocks the Marvel Universe as the rocky Thing, a powerhouse with a heart of gold and the backbone of the Fantastic Four.

data.headline: Thena
data.description: The fierce warrior Thena is more comfortable in battle than anywhere else.

data.headline: Thor
data.description: The son of Odin uses his mighty abilities as the God of Thunder to protect his home Asgard and planet Earth alike.

data.headline: Thunderball
data.description: A brilliant scientist turned brutal career criminal, Dr. Eliot Franklin has tunnel vision when it comes to his goals and a lust for power that has no bounds.

data.headline: Thunderbird
data.description: John Proudstar served as a United States Marine and then went on to fight for his fellow mutants thanks to the X-Men.

data.headline: Titania
data.description: With her superhuman strength, Titania takes every opportunity to prove herself as the strongest woman, often pitting herself against She-Hulk.

data.headline: Triton
data.description: At home underwater thanks to the massive transformation from the Terrigen Mists, Triton serves as the acquatic member of the Inhumans Royal Family.

data.headline: Tyesha Hillman
data.description: Tyesha Hillman is married to Aamir Khan, the brother of Kamala Khan, AKA Ms. Marvel.

data.headline: U.S.Agent
data.description: The patriotic flag flier U.S.Agent loves his country so much, he undergoes experimentation to gain superhuman strength and better fight for freedom.

data.headline: The Watcher
data.description: The Watcher is a being who exists outside the planes of space and time. He sees every moment that has happened, will happen, or is happening, and not just in our universe...

data.headline: Ultron
data.description: The creation gone awry, the sentient robot Ultron hates and seeks to wipe out humanity.

data.headline: Unum
data.secondary_text: Unum (the actual names of the beings that have been merged into her consciousness are unrevealed)

data.headline: Unus
data.secondary_text: Angelo Unuscione, legally changed to Gunther Bain

data.headline: Valentina Allegra de Fontaine
data.description: Valentina Allegra de Fontaine is a triple agent, secretly working for the terrorist organization Leviathan, while successfully infiltrating both S.H.I.E.L.D. and Hydra.

data.headline: Valeria Richards
data.description: Valeria Richards is a super-genius who uses her intellect to help her Super Hero parents and their team of protectors, the Fantastic Four.

data.headline: Valkyrie
data.description: Valkyrie uses her superhuman strength to defend Asgard.

data.headline: Valkyrie
data.description: Valkyrie uses her superhuman strength to defend Asgard.

data.headline: Vengeance
data.description: Touched by Ghost Rider Johnny Blaze, Deputy Kowalski went down a dark path to become Vengeance.

data.headline: Vengeance
data.description: Initially hell-bent on seeking his namesake, Vengeance eventually used his Ghost Rider-like powers for good.

data.headline: Venom
data.description: Bonding with an unearthly symbiote, Eddie Brock is given amazing powers and an unstable psyche.

data.headline: Victor Mancha
data.description: A cyborg/human hybrid, Victor Mancha can control electromagnetic energy.

data.headline: Vin Vision
data.description: Vin Vision is a synthezoid like his father and creator, the Avenger Vision, and learns how to live like in a world that’s resistant to accept him.

data.headline: Virginia Vision
data.description: Virginia Vision: synthezoid, mother, wife, and good neighbor until someone threatens her family, she becomes something else altogether.

data.headline: Vision
data.description: The android called Vision defies physics and fights as an Avenger with the power of density manipulation and his flawless computer brain.

data.headline: Vulture
data.description: Equipped with an impressive flying appartus, Adrian Toomes takes to the skies as the winged menace known as the Vulture.

data.headline: War Machine
data.description: Military veteran James Rhodes is ready for combat in his advanced armor, adding a formidable arsenal to Tony Stark-created designs.

data.headline: Ward Meachum
data.description: Part of a family known for both their business savvy and ruthless approach, Ward Meachum has struggled for power with the Iron Fist.

data.headline: Warlock
data.secondary_text: Warlock (English approximation of his name in his native language)

data.headline: Wasp
data.description: Showing the same scientific aptitude as her father, Hank Pym, Nadia Pym is inspired by both him and Janet van Dyne to fly into action as part of a new generation of heroes.

data.headline: Werewolf By Night
data.secondary_text: Jacob Russoff (given name), Jack Russell (adopted name)
data.description: During the day, Jack Russell appears as a man, but when the sun sets and the moon rises, he becomes Werewolf by Night!

data.headline: White Tiger
data.description: Ava Ayala becomes an avatar of the White Tiger God and acquires incredible powers, but she eventually breaks free of its influence to forge her own path as a hero.

data.headline: White Wolf
data.description: A loyal adopted son of Wakanda, White Wolf is the Chieftain of the Hatut Zeraze, the country’s secret police, and a brutal warrior.

data.headline: Wiccan
data.description: William “Billy” Kaplan, a young magician, not only faces confusion in his personal teenage life, but also in his attempts to become an official Super Hero.

data.headline: Winter Soldier
data.description: Bucky Barnes was brought back from his supposed death to be a brainwashed assassin called Winter Soldier. Reformed by his friends, he now fights alongside the Avengers.

data.headline: Wolverine
data.description: A mutant with an unstoppable healing power, adamantium metal claws and no-nonsense attitude makes the man called Logan, one of the most ferocious heroes in the universe.

data.headline: Wong
data.description: A master of the martial and mystic arts, Wong is a close companion of Doctor Strange.

data.headline: Wraith
data.description: The goth gunslinger known as Wraith is a warrior with a mission to hunt down his parents’ killer.

data.headline: The Wrecker
data.description: Thanks to a mystical crowbar, the Wrecker is a criminal turned Super Villain and violently maintains his power and leadership over his crooked cohort, the Wrecking Crew.

data.headline: Yo-Yo
data.description: The Inhuman speedster Elena runs circles around her enemies.

data.headline: Yon-Rogg
data.description: As the leader of a squad of elite Kree soldiers, Yon-Rogg takes newly-recruited Carol Danvers under his wing and trains her.

data.headline: Yondu
data.description: Adventurer and natural mystic, Yondu  wields a mighty bow with Yaka arrows that move according to his whistles.

data.headline: Yusuf Khan
data.description: Yusuf Khan is father to the brave polymorph Super Hero Kamala Khan, AKA Ms. Marvel.

data.headline: Zero
data.secondary_text: A.D.A.M. Unit (Ambient-Energy Dampening Actualization Module) Unit Zero

data.headline: Zoe Zimmer
data.description: The teenaged former bully turned supportive friend Zoe Zimmer always has her friends’ backs.
